<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='543961' id='t-543961'>Secondly, there had to be an acceptance</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='546383' id='t-546383'>that we were not going to be able to use</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='548339' id='t-548339'>all of this vacant land in the way that we had before</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='551203' id='t-551203'>and maybe for some time to come.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='553212' id='t-553212'>It wasn't going to be our traditional
residential neighborhoods</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='555777' id='t-555777'>as we had before,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='557394' id='t-557394'>and urban agriculture, while a very productive</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='560152' id='t-560152'>and successful intervention happening in Detroit,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='562844' id='t-562844'>was not the only answer,</span>
